# Li ecosystem gates (mandatory)

Agents **must** follow these before and during work. Style and structure are flexible; **gates are not**.

**Strict by default:** There is **no optional provability**. Proof, security, and performance run at maximum unless the user explicitly lowers via `li.toml` or documented env. Canonical: `docs/ecosystem/strict-by-default.md`, `.cursor/rules/li-strict-by-default.mdc`.

## Read order (start of session)

1. `docs/ecosystem/strict-by-default.md` (or `../roadmap/` when synced)
2. `../roadmap/docs/ecosystem/engineering-standards.md` (or sibling `roadmap/` checkout)
3. `../roadmap/docs/ecosystem/vision-and-roadmap.md`
4. `../roadmap/docs/ecosystem/agent-coordination.md` — `.li-agent-coord.json`, claims
5. `docs/superpowers/plans/2026-05-14-li-master-plan.md` in **`lic`** — current **PH-** phase
6. [Benchmarks dashboard](https://li-langverse.github.io/benchmarks/) — perf status
7. Latest **release notes** in target repo — `CHANGELOG.md` + `docs/release-notes/` (see **li-release-notes.mdc**)

## Three gates (every change)

| Gate | Evidence |
|------|----------|
| **Functionality** | `li-tests` / `lit` green; REQ/PH ids; contracts when phase requires |
| **Security** | Relevant CVE/CWE rows; `run_security.sh` / tier5 exploits; no trusted creep |
| **Performance** | Benchmark row or documented N/A; [benchmarks dashboard](https://li-langverse.github.io/benchmarks/) |

## Coverage tiers

| Scope | Line coverage |
|-------|---------------|
| **`std/**` in `lic`** | **100%** — `scripts/check-stdlib-coverage.sh` |
| **`lip publish` / official packages** | **≥80%** — `lit test --coverage` |
| **Experimental monorepo package** | SHOULD ≥80% before org promote |

## Design discipline

- New ecosystem feature: survey **2–4** mature systems; document **Learned from**; adapt to easy + AI-first + provable + fast.
- Cross-repo or pillar vision → **master plan** + roadmap **proposal**; not package README only.
- Org repos / secrets / branch protection → ask human; wait for confirmation.

## Org backup (agent experiment)

- **Never** run `scripts/backup-li-langverse-org.sh`, `export-li-langverse-metadata.sh`, or read `../.env.github.backup`.
- Human runbook: `docs/ecosystem/org-backup.md`.

## CI platforms (all OS must pass)

Canonical: `docs/ecosystem/ci-platforms.md`

- **Ubuntu, macOS, and Windows** CI jobs are **required** on `main` / PRs — same bar, no exceptions.
- **Forbidden:** `continue-on-error` (or equivalent) on OS build/test jobs to hide platform breakage.
- **Forbidden:** removing a platform from `.github/workflows/ci.yml` without human approval + tracked issue.
- On failure: **fix the platform** (LLVM install, paths, flags) — never merge “Linux-only green.”

## Escalate (do not do alone)

- Lower coverage tiers, skip CVE tests, weaken bench thresholds
- Non-blocking or dropped CI platform jobs
- New `trusted.lean` axioms
- Changing pillar priority or master plan phase order
- Weakening `agent-kit/hooks/guard-*.sh`

